notes.text:
An update for cups is now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 9.0 Extended Update Support.

Red Hat Product Security has rated this update as having a security impact of Important. A Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE link(s) in the References section.
notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
The Common UNIX Printing System (CUPS) provides a portable printing layer for Linux, UNIX, and similar operating systems.

Security Fix(es):

* cups: Information leak through Cups-Get-Document operation (CVE-2023-32360)

For more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.

cwe.name: Exposure of Sensitive Information to an Unauthorized Actor

notes.text: A vulnerability was found in OpenPrinting CUPS. Unauthorized users are permitted to fetch documents over local or remote networks, leading to confidentiality breach.
notes.title: Vulnerability description

notes.text:
This vulnerability is classified as important according to Red Hat's Severity Rating Classification, as unauthorized users are permitted to fetch documents over local or remote networks, leading to confidentiality breach.

https://access.redhat.com/security/updates/classification
notes.title: Statement

notes.text: The CVSS score(s) listed for this vulnerability do not reflect the associated product's status, and are included for informational purposes to better understand the severity of this vulnerability.
notes.title: CVSS score applicability

remediations.details:
For details on how to apply this update, which includes the changes described in this advisory, refer to:

https://access.redhat.com/articles/11258

After installing this update, the cupsd service will be restarted automatically.

The user can either set 'PreserveJobFiles No' in cupsd.conf which will completely shut off the saving the job files, thereby preventing the attacker to get a file or restrict access in firewall and in cupsd to trusted users.
